WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.359
9, verses 15-28.

00:00:02.359 --> 00:00:04.619
Really, as we look at the passage of Scripture,

00:00:04.619 --> 00:00:07.019
I'll begin reading in v. 15.

00:00:07.019 --> 00:00:10.600
We understand that part of the thought

00:00:10.600 --> 00:00:13.260
that we finished last week's message with

00:00:13.260 --> 00:00:15.319
is a continuation into this week.

00:00:15.319 --> 00:00:17.139
And so, we'll mention several things

00:00:17.139 --> 00:00:18.280
by way of introduction.

00:00:18.280 --> 00:00:20.079
But look at v. 15.

00:00:20.079 --> 00:00:20.840
The Bible says,

00:00:20.840 --> 00:00:22.180
"...and for this cause He,"

00:00:22.180 --> 00:00:23.780
speaking of the Lord Jesus Christ,

00:00:23.780 --> 00:00:25.079
God in flesh,

00:00:25.079 --> 00:00:27.860
"...He is the mediator of the New Testament,

00:00:27.860 --> 00:00:30.500
that by means of death,

00:00:30.500 --> 00:00:32.840
for the redemption of the transgressions

00:00:32.840 --> 00:00:35.439
that were under the first testament,

00:00:35.439 --> 00:00:38.459
they which are called might receive

00:00:38.459 --> 00:00:42.060
the promise of eternal inheritance.

00:00:42.060 --> 00:00:43.900
For where a testament is,"

00:00:43.900 --> 00:00:45.459
notice v. 16,

00:00:45.459 --> 00:00:48.740
"...there must also of necessity

00:00:48.740 --> 00:00:51.979
be the death of the testator.

00:00:51.979 --> 00:00:55.259
For a testament is of force after men are dead,

00:00:55.259 --> 00:00:58.659
but otherwise it is of no strength at all

00:00:58.659 --> 00:01:01.319
while the testator liveth."

00:01:01.319 --> 00:01:03.159
We look at this passage of Scripture.

00:01:03.159 --> 00:01:06.260
We'll actually go through the end of chapter 9 this morning.

00:01:06.260 --> 00:01:08.199
I've simply entitled the message there

00:01:08.199 --> 00:01:09.580
from v. 16-17,

00:01:09.580 --> 00:01:11.519
The Death of the Testator.

00:01:11.519 --> 00:01:13.919
And you look at the passage of Scripture

00:01:13.919 --> 00:01:16.059
and you understand the entirety

00:01:16.059 --> 00:01:18.099
of what we're dealing with in the book of Hebrews

00:01:18.099 --> 00:01:20.879
and the main thought and the subject matter

00:01:20.879 --> 00:01:24.860
and how the writer exalts the Lord Jesus Christ

00:01:24.860 --> 00:01:27.339
and proves His superiority.

00:01:27.339 --> 00:01:29.400
And what a joy to understand

00:01:29.400 --> 00:01:32.959
how these original recipients of this book

00:01:32.959 --> 00:01:34.559
that is titled Hebrews,

00:01:34.559 --> 00:01:36.559
and we are mindful of that

00:01:36.559 --> 00:01:37.919
which they were dealing with

00:01:37.919 --> 00:01:39.379
and the immense pressure

00:01:39.379 --> 00:01:41.180
to return to Judaism

00:01:41.180 --> 00:01:43.680
coupled with the fact that they were living

00:01:43.680 --> 00:01:46.080
under intensified persecution

00:01:46.080 --> 00:01:48.040
at the hand of Nero.

00:01:48.040 --> 00:01:49.940
And you think about those two factors

00:01:49.940 --> 00:01:52.160
and you think about all that they were dealing with

00:01:52.160 --> 00:01:54.959
and how the content of this book,

00:01:54.959 --> 00:01:56.180
the book of Hebrews,

00:01:56.180 --> 00:01:59.080
would provide them with encouragement.

00:01:59.080 --> 00:02:01.639
It would provide them with instruction.

00:02:01.639 --> 00:02:04.540
And we find this morning in 2020,

00:02:04.540 --> 00:02:07.660
a couple thousand years almost

00:02:07.660 --> 00:02:10.979
since the original writing of this book,

00:02:10.979 --> 00:02:13.360
we find that still today,

00:02:13.360 --> 00:02:17.119
the people of God are in need of encouragement.

00:02:17.119 --> 00:02:19.160
We're in need of instruction.

00:02:19.160 --> 00:02:21.580
And we find that the content of this book

00:02:21.600 --> 00:02:24.759
will help us in our daily walk with God.

00:02:24.759 --> 00:02:27.440
It will remind us over and over

00:02:27.440 --> 00:02:28.899
as we read the book of Hebrews,

00:02:28.899 --> 00:02:30.320
as we study the book of Hebrews,

00:02:30.320 --> 00:02:33.520
that Jesus is superior.

00:02:33.520 --> 00:02:35.160
He is better.

00:02:35.160 --> 00:02:39.199
There's nothing better than you're ever going to get.

00:02:39.199 --> 00:02:40.080
Amen?

00:02:40.080 --> 00:02:43.119
There's no other world system.

00:02:43.119 --> 00:02:45.279
There's no other religious system.

00:02:45.279 --> 00:02:47.580
There's no other thing

00:02:47.580 --> 00:02:50.220
that is better than Jesus.

00:02:50.220 --> 00:02:52.199
The reality, however,

00:02:52.199 --> 00:02:55.020
is that we have an enemy

00:02:55.020 --> 00:02:58.020
that is seeking to devour and destroy.

00:02:58.020 --> 00:03:01.240
We have an enemy that seeks to say to you

00:03:01.240 --> 00:03:02.940
and to say to me

00:03:02.940 --> 00:03:05.240
that this is better.

00:03:05.240 --> 00:03:08.199
Is it true?

00:03:08.199 --> 00:03:11.720
He walketh about seeking whom He may devour.

00:03:11.720 --> 00:03:13.679
And He says this is better.

00:03:13.679 --> 00:03:16.259
And we say, no, we have Jesus.

00:03:16.279 --> 00:03:20.440
Nothing is better than Jesus.

00:03:20.440 --> 00:03:23.520
No thing that the world can offer you

00:03:23.520 --> 00:03:26.360
is better than Jesus.

00:03:26.360 --> 00:03:30.559
No promotion, no person, no popularity.

00:03:30.559 --> 00:03:35.380
Nothing is better than Jesus.

00:03:35.380 --> 00:03:38.639
Not only does the passage of Scripture tell us

00:03:38.639 --> 00:03:41.520
as we study the book of Hebrews as a whole

00:03:41.520 --> 00:03:43.199
that Jesus is superior,

00:03:43.199 --> 00:03:45.139
but we find that after spending

00:03:45.139 --> 00:03:47.580
and laboring through 11 chapters

00:03:47.580 --> 00:03:48.779
and really the first 10,

00:03:48.779 --> 00:03:50.259
we know that in chapter 11,

00:03:50.259 --> 00:03:52.179
dealing with the example of those

00:03:52.179 --> 00:03:53.699
that lived by faith,

00:03:53.699 --> 00:03:56.339
we come and we find that the writer says

00:03:56.339 --> 00:03:59.500
because Jesus is so much better,

00:03:59.500 --> 00:04:01.179
because He is superior,

00:04:01.179 --> 00:04:03.880
look to Him.

00:04:03.880 --> 00:04:05.580
Looking unto Jesus.

00:04:05.580 --> 00:04:06.979
Our theme for this year

00:04:06.979 --> 00:04:08.740
from Hebrews 12.

00:04:08.740 --> 00:04:12.179
And we understand the truth of looking to Him.

00:04:12.360 --> 00:04:15.839
And can I tell you that as we gaze upon our Savior,

00:04:15.839 --> 00:04:18.880
as we fix our eyes upon our Savior,

00:04:18.880 --> 00:04:20.799
that the things of this world

00:04:20.799 --> 00:04:23.200
will grow strangely dim.

00:04:23.200 --> 00:04:27.000
The songwriter penned those words.

00:04:27.000 --> 00:04:29.079
Run your race.

00:04:29.079 --> 00:04:31.459
The truth from the book of Hebrews.

00:04:31.459 --> 00:04:35.359
Listen, he didn't say the race was going to be easy.

00:04:35.359 --> 00:04:38.920
He didn't say there would be no obstacles

00:04:38.920 --> 00:04:41.119
or hindrances.

00:04:41.140 --> 00:04:42.859
Difficulties along the way.

00:04:42.859 --> 00:04:45.940
But he said run your race when or how

00:04:45.940 --> 00:04:48.619
as you're looking to your Savior.

00:04:48.619 --> 00:04:51.100
And understanding that He will give you

00:04:51.100 --> 00:04:54.179
what you need to run that race.

00:04:54.179 --> 00:04:56.820
Paul said that there was an open door.

00:04:56.820 --> 00:04:57.820
Great and effectual.

00:04:57.820 --> 00:05:02.619
But there were many adversaries.

00:05:02.619 --> 00:05:05.140
We read throughout the passages

00:05:05.140 --> 00:05:06.260
of the Old Testament,

00:05:06.260 --> 00:05:08.540
we see how that as the work of God

00:05:08.540 --> 00:05:10.420
would go forward in the book of Ezra

00:05:10.420 --> 00:05:11.480
and Nehemiah,

00:05:11.480 --> 00:05:13.239
you find that they were constantly

00:05:13.239 --> 00:05:17.600
met with opposition.

00:05:17.600 --> 00:05:19.440
I believe that as we look at Hebrews,

00:05:19.440 --> 00:05:22.519
we are reminded that heaven is real.

00:05:22.519 --> 00:05:23.839
Heaven is real.

00:05:23.839 --> 00:05:26.040
This world is not my home.

00:05:26.040 --> 00:05:27.679
I'm just a passing through.

00:05:27.679 --> 00:05:30.239
We're looking for a better city.

00:05:30.239 --> 00:05:31.239
Heavenly.

00:05:31.239 --> 00:05:32.239
Amen?

00:05:32.239 --> 00:05:34.559
And as we come to look at the text

00:05:34.559 --> 00:05:36.799
of Hebrews as a whole, as a book,

00:05:36.899 --> 00:05:41.019
we are reminded of those great truths of Scripture.

00:05:41.019 --> 00:05:43.500
And we continue in this 9th chapter

00:05:43.500 --> 00:05:46.100
and we find that here as we're going

00:05:46.100 --> 00:05:48.459
through this process and the reality

00:05:48.459 --> 00:05:49.739
this morning as we get in really

00:05:49.739 --> 00:05:50.739
to the beginning of the message

00:05:50.739 --> 00:05:54.459
is that we find that for us today,

00:05:54.459 --> 00:05:56.380
that we look at the cross

00:05:56.380 --> 00:05:59.100
as being something wonderful.

00:05:59.100 --> 00:06:00.540
Because we understand that it was there

00:06:00.540 --> 00:06:04.019
at the cross that my Savior bled and died.

00:06:04.019 --> 00:06:06.540
It was there at the cross that He did

00:06:06.559 --> 00:06:10.880
that which He had come to this earth to do.

00:06:10.880 --> 00:06:12.440
But you understand for the Jewish people

00:06:12.440 --> 00:06:14.359
at the original time of this writing,

00:06:14.359 --> 00:06:16.119
in fact, many times even still today

00:06:16.119 --> 00:06:18.359
as we see in the book of 1 Corinthians,

00:06:18.359 --> 00:06:22.279
that the cross is a stumbling block.

00:06:22.279 --> 00:06:25.239
They ask this question immediately

00:06:25.239 --> 00:06:28.839
following the timing of the life and death

00:06:28.839 --> 00:06:30.399
and of course the resurrection

00:06:30.399 --> 00:06:31.519
and the ascension of Christ

00:06:31.519 --> 00:06:33.079
and all that's moving forward

00:06:33.079 --> 00:06:34.440
with the early church

00:06:34.440 --> 00:06:35.640
and all that's taking place

00:06:35.660 --> 00:06:37.739
and you find that there are many

00:06:37.739 --> 00:06:41.980
that would say, why did He have to die?

00:06:41.980 --> 00:06:44.299
The death of Christ really kind of

00:06:44.299 --> 00:06:47.820
adversely affected many that were Jews.

00:06:47.820 --> 00:06:49.500
Why? Because they were looking for a Messiah

00:06:49.500 --> 00:06:51.179
who was going to set up a kingdom,

00:06:51.179 --> 00:06:52.660
who was going to deal with the Romans,

00:06:52.660 --> 00:06:54.059
who was going to do all of those things

00:06:54.059 --> 00:06:57.500
and they missed the fact that the Old Testament

00:06:57.500 --> 00:07:01.820
had consistently given the truth,

00:07:01.820 --> 00:07:03.739
the picture, the typology

00:07:03.760 --> 00:07:06.000
that the Messiah would die

00:07:06.000 --> 00:07:08.160
for the sins of the world.

00:07:08.160 --> 00:07:10.320
And so as we look at this passage of Scripture,

00:07:10.320 --> 00:07:14.519
we find that as the writer is kind of again

00:07:14.519 --> 00:07:17.160
peeling back another peel of the onion

00:07:17.160 --> 00:07:19.959
and providing another glimpse

00:07:19.959 --> 00:07:22.679
into the understanding that He's better.

00:07:22.679 --> 00:07:24.959
Why? He's a better priest

00:07:24.959 --> 00:07:26.959
and He served in a better place, right?

00:07:26.959 --> 00:07:28.839
The sanctuary in heaven.

00:07:28.839 --> 00:07:30.600
That true tabernacle.

00:07:30.600 --> 00:07:33.600
He presented a better offering.

00:07:33.619 --> 00:07:35.579
It was His own blood.

00:07:35.579 --> 00:07:39.079
And we find that He gave us through that

00:07:39.079 --> 00:07:41.299
a better gift.

00:07:41.299 --> 00:07:42.700
And as we look at the truth

00:07:42.700 --> 00:07:44.940
of what the passage that we're dealing with

00:07:44.940 --> 00:07:46.540
in Hebrews 9 is dealing with,

00:07:46.540 --> 00:07:48.579
we come and we notice first of all,

00:07:48.579 --> 00:07:50.640
if you're taking notes,

00:07:50.640 --> 00:07:51.899
it's the bulk of the section

00:07:51.899 --> 00:07:53.100
in which we'll be dealing with.

00:07:53.100 --> 00:07:54.380
In fact, as I mentioned,

00:07:54.380 --> 00:07:56.820
that really the latter part of last week's message

00:07:56.820 --> 00:07:58.140
goes right into it.

00:07:58.140 --> 00:07:59.380
And it's this, number one,

00:07:59.380 --> 00:08:02.579
notice the atonement of Christ.

00:08:03.559 --> 00:08:06.320
That word atonement is the expiation of sin

00:08:06.320 --> 00:08:11.320
made by the obedience and suffering of Christ.

00:08:11.320 --> 00:08:14.200
We understand when we speak about the death of Christ,

00:08:14.200 --> 00:08:17.200
we understand that as He said there in John 17,

00:08:17.200 --> 00:08:18.760
the hour has come.

00:08:18.760 --> 00:08:21.119
Jesus understood the purpose

00:08:21.119 --> 00:08:22.920
in which He came to this earth.

00:08:22.920 --> 00:08:24.839
In fact, earlier in the book of John,

00:08:24.839 --> 00:08:27.160
He mentions about destroying this temple

00:08:27.160 --> 00:08:29.160
and in three days I'll raise it up.

00:08:29.160 --> 00:08:31.040
And speaking of His own body

00:08:31.040 --> 00:08:32.479
and of course, not only the death,

00:08:32.539 --> 00:08:33.900
but the resurrection.

00:08:33.900 --> 00:08:35.619
You remember that during the time

00:08:35.619 --> 00:08:37.099
in which the Lord Jesus Christ

00:08:37.099 --> 00:08:39.340
interacted with His disciples and He said,

00:08:39.340 --> 00:08:41.059
whom do men say that I am?

00:08:41.059 --> 00:08:44.580
And then He says, but who do you say that I am?

00:08:44.580 --> 00:08:47.059
And after Peter stands up with great boldness

00:08:47.059 --> 00:08:49.500
and says, thou art the Christ,

00:08:49.500 --> 00:08:51.520
the Son of the living God,

00:08:51.520 --> 00:08:52.820
we find that Jesus,

00:08:52.820 --> 00:08:54.700
if you look at the text of Scripture,

00:08:54.700 --> 00:08:56.500
He then began to share with them

00:08:56.500 --> 00:08:58.979
the things that would shortly come to pass

00:08:59.039 --> 00:09:00.320
concerning what?

00:09:00.320 --> 00:09:04.719
His death and His resurrection.

00:09:04.719 --> 00:09:06.440
And so we notice the atonement of Christ

00:09:06.440 --> 00:09:08.039
as we look at those few verses

00:09:08.039 --> 00:09:08.960
that we've mentioned.

00:09:08.960 --> 00:09:10.440
Actually, back up into verse 12.

00:09:10.440 --> 00:09:11.200
The Bible says,

00:09:11.200 --> 00:09:13.039
neither by the blood of goats and calves,

00:09:13.039 --> 00:09:14.159
but by His own blood,

00:09:14.159 --> 00:09:17.760
He entered in once into the holy place,

00:09:17.760 --> 00:09:21.919
having obtained eternal redemption for us.

00:09:21.919 --> 00:09:23.880
Remember, He went to a better place,

00:09:23.880 --> 00:09:26.479
the heavenly tabernacle.

00:09:26.479 --> 00:09:28.320
He offered a better sacrifice.

00:09:28.340 --> 00:09:29.539
It was His own blood,

00:09:29.539 --> 00:09:31.460
not the blood of bulls and goats.

00:09:31.460 --> 00:09:34.739
And we find that He obtained for us

00:09:34.739 --> 00:09:39.619
a better gift, eternal redemption.

00:09:39.619 --> 00:09:41.580
We see it unfolded in verse 12.

00:09:41.580 --> 00:09:44.020
The Bible says that He entered in once.

00:09:44.020 --> 00:09:45.380
As I mentioned last week,

00:09:45.380 --> 00:09:46.900
as we look at that phraseology

00:09:46.900 --> 00:09:48.580
and we even couple it with what we find

00:09:48.580 --> 00:09:50.020
in verse 26,

00:09:50.020 --> 00:09:51.900
the latter part of verse 26,

00:09:51.900 --> 00:09:55.619
but now once in the end of the world

00:09:55.619 --> 00:09:57.299
hath He appeared to put away sin

00:09:57.299 --> 00:09:59.859
by the sacrifice of Himself.

00:09:59.859 --> 00:10:02.159
It's interesting as we understand

00:10:02.159 --> 00:10:04.419
the beginning of the ninth chapter

00:10:04.419 --> 00:10:05.619
of the book of Hebrews

00:10:05.619 --> 00:10:09.019
dealing with the earthly tabernacle

00:10:09.019 --> 00:10:10.659
and dealing with the holy place

00:10:10.659 --> 00:10:11.819
and the Holy of Holies.

00:10:11.819 --> 00:10:13.019
And I told you last week

00:10:13.019 --> 00:10:14.459
that what was in view

00:10:14.459 --> 00:10:16.979
was really the Day of Atonement.

00:10:16.979 --> 00:10:19.139
And it's interesting because we understand

00:10:19.139 --> 00:10:21.059
that it says that He entered in once.

00:10:21.059 --> 00:10:23.539
Not only did He only go in once,

00:10:23.539 --> 00:10:25.259
but He only had to do it once.

00:10:25.259 --> 00:10:26.539
Once for all.

00:10:26.539 --> 00:10:27.859
The High Priest,

00:10:27.859 --> 00:10:30.059
when He would go in on the Day of Atonement,

00:10:30.059 --> 00:10:32.299
He would enter in that first time

00:10:32.299 --> 00:10:34.739
to present the blood of a bull

00:10:34.739 --> 00:10:36.659
for His own sins.

00:10:36.659 --> 00:10:38.859
And then He would come out

00:10:38.859 --> 00:10:42.299
and He'd have to go in a second time.

00:10:42.299 --> 00:10:44.579
Look at Leviticus 16. You can see it.

00:10:44.579 --> 00:10:46.139
With the blood of the goat.

00:10:46.139 --> 00:10:48.339
Why? For the sins of the people.

00:10:48.339 --> 00:10:50.259
Jesus had no sin.

00:10:50.259 --> 00:10:52.179
The just for the unjust.

00:10:52.179 --> 00:10:54.899
Therefore, He only had to enter

00:10:54.899 --> 00:10:58.379
into the Holy of Holies once

00:10:58.379 --> 00:11:01.179
to present His perfect, sinless blood.

00:11:01.179 --> 00:11:02.459
And by the way,

00:11:02.459 --> 00:11:05.379
as you look at the truth of the Day of Atonement,

00:11:05.379 --> 00:11:07.339
not only did the High Priest go in twice

00:11:07.339 --> 00:11:08.699
on that same day,

00:11:08.699 --> 00:11:10.779
but then next year it would have to be repeated

00:11:10.779 --> 00:11:14.419
and the year after that and the year after that.

00:11:14.419 --> 00:11:17.739
But with the sacrifice of Jesus, it's not so.

00:11:17.739 --> 00:11:19.859
We see the atonement of Christ.

00:11:19.859 --> 00:11:20.979
It's in full view.

00:11:20.979 --> 00:11:23.819
We understand that it's a substitutionary atonement.

00:11:23.859 --> 00:11:25.339
He took your place.

00:11:25.339 --> 00:11:26.419
He took my place.

00:11:26.419 --> 00:11:28.379
We understand that it was a blood atonement

00:11:28.379 --> 00:11:31.099
as we continue looking through the passage of Scripture.

00:11:31.099 --> 00:11:34.019
Pick it up with me in verse 18.

00:11:34.019 --> 00:11:34.859
The Bible says,

00:11:34.859 --> 00:11:36.619
"...whereupon neither the First Testament

00:11:36.619 --> 00:11:38.819
was dedicated without blood.

00:11:38.819 --> 00:11:40.939
Notice, for when Moses had spoken

00:11:40.939 --> 00:11:42.899
every precept to all the people

00:11:42.899 --> 00:11:44.179
according to the law,

00:11:44.179 --> 00:11:46.779
he took the blood of calves and of goats

00:11:46.779 --> 00:11:49.699
with water and scarlet wool and hyssop

00:11:49.699 --> 00:11:52.379
and sprinkled both the book and all the people,

00:11:52.419 --> 00:11:55.099
saying, this is the blood of the Testament

00:11:55.099 --> 00:11:58.419
which God hath enjoined unto you.

00:11:58.419 --> 00:12:00.859
Moreover, he sprinkled with blood

00:12:00.859 --> 00:12:02.899
both the tabernacle and all the vessels

00:12:02.899 --> 00:12:04.299
of the ministry.

00:12:04.299 --> 00:12:05.899
And almost all things are by the law

00:12:05.899 --> 00:12:07.579
purged with blood,

00:12:07.579 --> 00:12:12.139
