00:12:12.139 --> 00:12:13.939
What is the writer saying to these believers?

00:12:13.939 --> 00:12:15.779
What is he saying to us this morning?

00:12:15.779 --> 00:12:20.019
The death of Christ was absolutely necessary.

00:12:20.059 --> 00:12:22.459
We find that as we read in v. 16,

00:12:22.459 --> 00:12:24.539
it says for where a Testament is,

00:12:24.539 --> 00:12:27.179
there must also of necessity

00:12:27.179 --> 00:12:30.019
be the death of the testator.

00:12:30.019 --> 00:12:32.179
As we understand that truth

00:12:32.179 --> 00:12:33.779
and we understand through His death

00:12:33.779 --> 00:12:35.299
and glorious resurrection

00:12:35.299 --> 00:12:37.819
that the promise of eternal redemption

00:12:37.819 --> 00:12:40.459
can now be received.

00:12:40.459 --> 00:12:43.099
See, the reality is that at the end of v. 15,

00:12:43.099 --> 00:12:45.099
it says they which are called

00:12:45.099 --> 00:12:49.459
might receive the promise of eternal inheritance.

00:12:49.499 --> 00:12:50.939
Remember, in v. 12,

00:12:50.939 --> 00:12:52.339
He said that He had obtained

00:12:52.339 --> 00:12:55.819
eternal redemption for us.

00:12:55.819 --> 00:12:59.019
How many of you have a will?

00:12:59.019 --> 00:13:00.499
