00:13:02.539 --> 00:13:05.019
I'm not trying to get anything on the side.

00:13:05.019 --> 00:13:07.619
I'm just simply saying it's common, right?

00:13:07.619 --> 00:13:10.419
People have wills.

00:13:10.419 --> 00:13:13.899
The reality is that if you have a will,

00:13:13.899 --> 00:13:17.179
until you are deceased,

00:13:17.219 --> 00:13:19.419
it is not in effect.

00:13:19.419 --> 00:13:21.419
Correct?

00:13:21.419 --> 00:13:22.939
In fact, I am often reminded,

00:13:22.939 --> 00:13:24.699
though my dad's not here this morning,

00:13:24.699 --> 00:13:26.219
I believe he's watching live stream,

00:13:26.219 --> 00:13:28.699
he has a will.

00:13:28.699 --> 00:13:30.099
And he'll say something like this

00:13:30.099 --> 00:13:31.579
every once in a while.

00:13:31.579 --> 00:13:34.579
I'm going to change my will.

00:13:34.579 --> 00:13:35.859
Right? Doesn't he?

00:13:35.859 --> 00:13:37.739
Taking you out of my will.

00:13:37.739 --> 00:13:39.579
Why can he say that?

00:13:39.579 --> 00:13:42.739
Because he's still alive.

00:13:42.739 --> 00:13:43.659
You have a will.

00:13:43.659 --> 00:13:46.579
It can be changed if you're alive.

00:13:46.619 --> 00:13:50.859
What probates the will is the death.

00:13:50.859 --> 00:13:52.299
Correct?

00:13:52.299 --> 00:13:54.219
So understand that as we're looking

00:13:54.219 --> 00:13:55.859
at the passage of Scripture,

00:13:55.859 --> 00:13:58.299
and we find that the writer of Hebrews

00:13:58.299 --> 00:14:01.579
is presenting to these Jewish believers

00:14:01.579 --> 00:14:04.459
that it was absolutely imperative,

00:14:04.459 --> 00:14:08.939
it was necessary for Christ to die.

00:14:08.939 --> 00:14:12.099
We find that all the way back in Genesis.

00:14:12.099 --> 00:14:13.739
We find that in chapter 3,

00:14:13.739 --> 00:14:15.179
when sin entered into the world,

00:14:15.219 --> 00:14:17.619
you see the truth in Genesis 3

00:14:17.619 --> 00:14:20.979
in verse 15 concerning the first mention

00:14:20.979 --> 00:14:22.979
of the truth that God Himself,

00:14:22.979 --> 00:14:24.500
the Lord Jesus Christ,

00:14:24.500 --> 00:14:27.779
would die for the sins of man.

00:14:27.779 --> 00:14:30.259
You find that there in Genesis 3,

00:14:30.259 --> 00:14:32.379
immediately after Adam and Eve

00:14:32.379 --> 00:14:33.779
committed the sin,

00:14:33.779 --> 00:14:34.779
what did they try to do?

00:14:34.779 --> 00:14:36.299
They tried to cover it with the works

00:14:36.299 --> 00:14:37.419
of their own hands,

00:14:37.419 --> 00:14:39.819
with the fig leaves that they sowed together,

00:14:39.819 --> 00:14:43.539
but it was not accepted.

00:14:43.539 --> 00:14:45.019
What did God do?

00:14:45.099 --> 00:14:47.059
He sacrificed an animal

00:14:47.059 --> 00:14:51.219
and He made a coat of skins.

00:14:51.219 --> 00:14:52.500
From that day forward,

00:14:52.500 --> 00:14:55.779
you read, as you think about Cain and Abel,

00:14:55.779 --> 00:14:58.339
the reality of the accepted offering

00:14:58.339 --> 00:15:00.779
was the one that was blood.

00:15:00.779 --> 00:15:02.739
And you go through the whole

00:15:02.739 --> 00:15:03.859
of the Old Testament,

00:15:03.859 --> 00:15:06.539
and you see that God has designed it

00:15:06.539 --> 00:15:09.179
such that without shedding of blood

00:15:09.179 --> 00:15:11.579
is no remission.

00:15:11.579 --> 00:15:13.459
And therefore, God Himself,

00:15:13.459 --> 00:15:14.659
the Lord Jesus Christ,

00:15:14.699 --> 00:15:16.939
He would go to the cross of Calvary

00:15:16.939 --> 00:15:19.379
and He would shed His precious blood

00:15:19.379 --> 00:15:22.339
so that that which He had promised

00:15:22.339 --> 00:15:25.859
could be obtained.

00:15:25.859 --> 00:15:28.419
We find that what had been pictured

00:15:28.419 --> 00:15:31.699
has now been purchased.

00:15:31.699 --> 00:15:33.939
We find the necessity.

00:15:33.939 --> 00:15:35.739
We see the Old Testament type

00:15:35.739 --> 00:15:37.739
in the verses that we just read

00:15:37.739 --> 00:15:38.979
speaking of Moses

00:15:38.979 --> 00:15:43.739
and how He took and He sprinkled that blood.

00:15:43.739 --> 00:15:45.259
The people. The book.

00:15:45.259 --> 00:15:46.299
And all that He did.

00:15:46.299 --> 00:15:48.099
He talks about the fact that He

00:15:48.099 --> 00:15:50.219
did all those vessels of the ministry.

00:15:50.219 --> 00:15:52.339
And you look back in the books of Exodus

00:15:52.339 --> 00:15:53.179
and Leviticus,

00:15:53.179 --> 00:15:54.939
and you see the carrying out

00:15:54.939 --> 00:15:58.459
and the reference in which the writer is making.

00:15:58.459 --> 00:15:59.739
And we're mindful this morning

00:15:59.739 --> 00:16:01.699
of this wonderful truth again

00:16:01.699 --> 00:16:04.179
as we think about the death of Christ

00:16:04.179 --> 00:16:05.899
and His glorious resurrection.

00:16:05.899 --> 00:16:07.779
We find that the offering of Himself

00:16:07.779 --> 00:16:09.819
was accepted.

00:16:09.819 --> 00:16:12.459
It was an acceptable offering.

00:16:12.459 --> 00:16:14.500
In verse 23 of our text of Scripture,

00:16:14.500 --> 00:16:14.939
it says,

00:16:14.939 --> 00:16:16.500
it was therefore necessary...

00:16:16.500 --> 00:16:17.819
We see that word again.

00:16:17.819 --> 00:16:20.459
That the patterns of things in the heavens

00:16:20.459 --> 00:16:22.739
should be purified with these,

00:16:22.739 --> 00:16:24.619
